name: Lunges
title: The lunge is a popular leg-strengthening exercise with a multitude of variations to add variety to your workout.

name: Pushups
title: Traditional pushups are beneficial for building upper body strength. They work the triceps, pectoral muscles, and shoulders.

name: Squats
title: The squat is considered a compound movement, meaning it works multiple muscle groups across multiple joints.

name: Overhead dumbbell
title: The overhead dumbbell press increases strength throughout the entire shoulder region. Performing the exercise from the standing position will actively engage the core throughout the range of motion.

name: Dumbbell rows
title: Blowing up your back muscles takes work, and one of the simplest, best, and most popular exercises to get it done are dumbbell rows.

name: Burpees
title: An exercise we love to hate, burpees are a super-effective, whole-body move that provides great bang for your buck for cardiovascular endurance and muscle strength.

name: Side planks
title: The side plank works a couple of key muscle groups that are often neglected by even the best abs exercises, such as crunches.

name: Planks
title: Planks are an effective way to target both your abdominal muscles and your whole body. Planking stabilizes your core without straining your back the way situps or crunches might.

name: Glute bridge
title: The glute bridge effectively works your entire posterior chain, which isn’t only good for you, but it’ll make your booty look perkier, too.
